{
  "texts": [
    "Facts 2.38 and 4.49).",
    "◁Recall that the operation of powerset possibilization captures the view that the space of possibilities is the space of nonempty sets of worlds.",
    "This view builds in strong assumptions about the nature of possibilities, e.g., that the space of possibilities ordered by refinement has the structure of a complete and atomic Boolean lattice (minus the minimum element).",
    "Using these properties and one other property concerning the interplay of accessibility and refinement, we can characterize the class of possibility frames that are isomorphic to the powerset possibilization of some Kripke frame, as in § 4.7.",
    "In § 4.7 we will also explain that any full possibility frame can be transformed into a semantically equivalent possibility frame that shares several of the properties of powerset possibilizations, with the exception of atomicity."
  ]
}